quran[27]{c,v,t,f}:
  68,46,"Or do you ask of them a payment, so they are by debt burdened down?"
  68,47,"Or have they [knowledge of] the unseen, so they write [it] down?"
  68,48,"Then be patient for the decision of your Lord, [O Muḥammad], and be not like the companion of the fish [i.e., Jonah] when he called out while he was distressed."
  69,43,"[It is] a revelation from the Lord of the worlds."
  69,44,"And if he [i.e., Muḥammad] had made up about Us some [false] sayings,"
  69,45,"We would have seized him by the right hand;{1}",footnotes:1:Another interpretation is "by [Our] right hand," i.e., Allāh would have exacted revenge with might and power.
  70,37,"[To sit] on [your] right and [your] left in separate groups?{1}",footnotes:1:They sat at a distance in order to oppose and mock the Prophet (ﷺ), claiming that they would enter Paradise before the believers.
  70,38,"Does every person among them aspire to enter a garden of pleasure?"
  70,39,"No! Indeed, We have created them from that which they know.{1}",footnotes:1:i.e., a liquid disdained.  So how can they expect to enter Paradise except by the will of their Creator?
  74,22,"Then he frowned and scowled;"
  74,23,"Then he turned back and was arrogant"
  74,24,"And said, "
  75,19,"Then upon Us is its clarification [to you]."
  75,20,"No! But you [i.e., mankind] love the immediate"
  75,21,"And leave [i.e., neglect] the Hereafter."
  76,13,"[They will be] reclining therein on adorned couches. They will not see therein any [burning] sun or [freezing] cold."
  76,14,"And near above them are its shades, and its [fruit] to be picked will be lowered in compliance."
  76,15,"And there will be circulated among them vessels of silver and cups having been [created] clear [as glass],"
  77,10,"And when the mountains are blown away"
  77,11,"And when the messengers' time has come...{1}",footnotes:1:i.e., when they are gathered to witness concerning their nations.  The sentence's conclusion is understood to be "...the promised judgement will then take place."
  77,12,"For what Day was it postponed?{1}",footnotes:1:"It" may refer to either the aforementioned occurrences collectively or to the testimony of the messengers.
  78,7,"And the mountains as stakes?{1}",footnotes:1:To stabilize the land and balance the earth.
  78,8,"And We created you in pairs."
  78,9,"And made your sleep [a means for] rest"
  79,1,"By those [angels] who extract with violence{1}",footnotes:1:i.e., those who tear out the souls of those destined for Hell.
  79,2,"And [by] those who remove with ease{1}",footnotes:1:i.e., those angels who ease out the souls of those destined for Paradise.
  79,3,"And [by] those who glide [as if] swimming{1}",footnotes:1:Speeding to execute Allāh's commands.